s a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view ratan tata  wikipedia ratan tata from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search ratan tata ratan tata born   december  age  mumbai residence colaba mumbai india nationality indian alma mater cornell university harvard business school occupation former chairman tata group  relatives see tata family awards padma vibhushan ratan naval tata born  december  is an indian industrialist investor philanthropist and former chairman of tata sons he was the chairman of tata group a mumbaibased global business conglomerate from  till  and again from  october  for an interim term and continues to head its charitable trusts he is the recipient of two of the highest civilian awards of india–padma vibhushan  and padma bhushan  he is an alumnus of the prestigious cathedral and john connon school bishop cotton school shimla cornell university  harvard business school contents  early life  career  philanthropy  tata hall  board memberships and affiliations  honours and awards  references  external links early lifeedit main article tata family ratan tata is the son of naval tata who had been adopted from j n petit parsi orphanage by navajbai tata his parents naval and sonoo separated in  when he was ten and his younger brother jimmy was seven years old both he and his brother were raised by their grandmother navajbai tata he has a halfbrother noel tata from naval tatas second marriage to simone tata he schooled in mumbai and shimla at the cathedral and john connon school and bishop cotton school shimla he received a b arch degree in architecture with structural engineering from cornell university in  and the advanced management program from harvard business school in  careeredit tata began his career in the tata group in  he started on the shop floor of tata steel shovelling limestone and handling the blast furnace he could not turn around group companies nelco and empress mills which he was given charge of in the s in  j r d tata stepped down as chairman of tata sons naming him his successor when he settled down into the new role he faced stiff resistance from many company heads some of whom had spent decades in their respective companies and rose to become very powerful and influential due to the freedom to operate under jrd tata he began replacing them by setting a retirement age and then made individual companies report operationally to the group office and made each contribute some of their profit to build and use the tata group brand innovation was given priority and younger talent was infused and given responsibilities under his stewardship overlapping operations in group companies were streamlined into a synergised whole with the salttosoftware group exiting unrelated businesses to take on the onslaught of globalisation during the  years he led the tata group revenues grew over  times and profit over  times where sales of the group as a whole overwhelmingly came from commodities when he took over the majority sales came from brands when he exited he boldly got tata tea to acquire tetley tata motors to acquire jaguar land rover and tata steel to acquire corus all this turned tata from a largely indiacentric group into a global business with over  revenues coming from operations and sales in over  countries he conceptualised the tata nano car as he explained in a recentwhen interview for the harvard business schools creating emerging markets project the development of the tata nano was significant because it helped put cars at a pricepoint within reach of the average indian consumer ratan tata relinquished all executive power in the tata group on  december  on turning  appointing as his successor cyrus mistry the yearold son of pallonji mistry of the shapoorji pallonji group the largest individual shareholder of the group and related by marriage on  october  cyrus mistry was removed as the chairman of tata sons and ratan tata was made interim chairman the decision went through intense media scrutiny that made many scrutinize the root causes of the sudden removal and the resultant crisis on  january  natarajan chandrasekaran was named as the chairman of tata sons a role he will assume in february  recently he invested his personal savings in snapdeal  one of indias leading ecommerce website and in jan  made an undisclosed funding in teabox — an online store selling premium indian tea  and cashkarocom — an online discount coupons and cashback website ratan tata has been making small investments in both early and late stage companies in india he made investments of inr  cr in ola cabs and inr  cr in paytm in april  it was reported that tata had acquired a stake in chinese smartphone startup xiaomi with specific terms undisclosed in october  he partnered with american express in investing in bitcoin venture abra in jan  it was reported that ratan tata invested in an online pet care portal called dogspot philanthropyedit tata halledit in the fall of  hbs tata related companies and charities donated  million for the construction of an executive center the executive center have been named as tata hall after ratan tata amp  the chairman of tata sons the total construction costs have been estimated at  million the tata hall is located in the northeast corner of the hbs campus the facility is devoted to the harvard business schools midcareer executive education program it is seven stories tall with about  gross square feet it houses approximately  bedrooms in addition to academic and multipurpose spaces board memberships and affiliationsedit he is the interim chairman of tata sons he continues to head the main two tata trusts sir dorabji tata trust and sir ratan tata trust and their allied trusts with a combined stake of  in tata sons tata groups holding company he has served in various capacities in organisations in india and abroad he is a member of the prime ministers council on trade and industry and the national manufacturing competitiveness council he is on the jury panel of pritzker architecture prize – considered to be one of the worlds premier architecture prizes he is a director on the boards of alcoa inc mondelez international and board of governors of the eastwest center he is also a member of the board of trustees of university of southern california harvard business school board of deans advisors x prize and cornell university he is a member on the board of international advisory council at bocconi university he is also a member of the harvard business school india advisory board iab since  and previously a member of the harvard business school asiapacific advisory board apab  in february  ratan took an advisory role at kalari capitalcitation needed recently ratan tata has also invested an undisclosed amount in nestaway in february   in october  tata sons removed cyrus mistry as its chairman nearly  years after he took over the reins of the over  billion conglomerate ratan tata made a come back taking over the companys interim boss for  months a selection committee has been formed to find a successor in four months the selection committee comprising mr tata tvs group head venu srinivasan amit chandra of bain capital former diplomat ronen sen and lord kumar bhattacharya all of them except mr bhattacharya are on the board of tata sons honours and awardsedit ratan tata received the padma vibhushan in  and padma bhushan in  the second and third highest civilian honours awarded by the government of india the other notable awards are year name awarding organisation ref  commander of the legion of honour government of france   sayaji ratna award baroda management association honoris causa hec paris   honorary doctor of automotive engineering clemson university   honorary doctor of laws york university canada   honorary knight grand cross of the most excellent order of the british empire gbe united kingdom government   sayaji ratna award baroda management association   honorary doctor of business singapore management university   honorary doctorate university of amsterdam   honorary doctor of business practice carnegie mellon university   ernst and young entrepreneur of the year – lifetime achievement ernst  young   transformational leader of the decade indian affairs india leadership conclave    foreign associate national academy of engineering   grand cordon of the order of the rising sun government of japan   doctor of business honoris causa university of new south wales   honorary fellow the royal academy of engineering   business leader of the year the asian awards   business for peace award business for peace foundation   honorary doctor of laws pepperdine university   legend in leadership award yale university   oslo business for peace award business for peace foundation   hadrian award world monuments fund   honorary doctor of law university of cambridge   grand officer of the order of merit of the italian republic italy   life time contribution award in engineering for  indian national academy of engineering   honorary knight commander of the order of the british empire kbe united kingdom   inspired leadership award the performance theatre   honorary fellowship the institution of engineering and technology   honorary citizen award government of singapore    honorary doctor of science indian institute of technology kharagpur   honorary doctor of science indian institute of technology bombay   honorary doctor of law university of cambridge   carnegie medal of philanthropy carnegie endowment for international peace   honorary fellowship the london school of economics and political science   responsible capitalism award first   honorary doctor of science indian institute of technology madras   honorary doctor of science university of warwick   international distinguished achievement award bnai brith international   honorary doctor of technology asian institute of technology   medal of the oriental republic of uruguay government of uruguay   honorary doctor of business administration ohio state university  referencesedit  the amazing story of how ratan tata built an empire rediff  october   httpwwwtatacomarticleinsidetatasonschairmanselectioncommittee  ratan tata is chairman emeritus of tata sons the times of india   masani zareer  february  what makes the tata empire tick the independent uk retrieved  april    a b c list of fellows — royal academy of engineering raengorguk retrieved    langley william  march  ratan tata rode the tiger economy and now he drives jaguar the daily telegraph london retrieved  march    ratan tata goes back to school times of india  march  retrieved  march    chidanand rajghatta  december  times of india article man of the year its ratan tata the times of india retrieved  october    a b c majumdar shyamal  january   years ago  and now ratan tata increased dare quotient of tata group business standard retrieved  april    ratan tata and nelco crucible – the untold story vivifychangecatalyst  october  retrieved  april    a b christopher elizabeth deresky helen  international management managing cultural diversity second ed pearson australia p  isbn  retrieved  april    the tata group out of india the economist  mar  retrieved  april    aiyar shankkar  february  ratans tata india today retrieved  april    goldstein andrea january  the internationalization of indian companies the case of tata center for the advanced study of india university of pennsylvania p  retrieved  april    mithas s  making the elephant dance the tata way to innovate transform and globalize kindle version is available at httpwwwamazonindpbgmsca new delhi penguin portfolio  interview with ratan naval tata creating emerging markets harvard business school   cyrus p mistry to succeed ratan tata retrieved  november    ratan tata indias corporate czar retires with a  billion vision bloomberg retriev