in – the revenue of tata companies altogether was  billion these companies collectively employ over  people each tata company or enterprise operates independently under the guidance and supervision of its own board of directors and shareholders there are  publicly listed tata enterprises with a combined market capitalisation of about  billion as of march  tata companies with significant scale include tata steel tata motors tata consultancy services tata power tata chemicals tata global beverages tata teleservices titan tata communications and taj group contents  chairman  subsidiaries  philanthropy  controversies and criticisms  munnar kerala  kalinganagar odisha  supplies to burmas military regime  land acquisition in singur  dhamra port odisha  soda extraction plant in tanzania  data and intellectual property theft  fire breakout at headquarters  see also  references  external links chairmanedit jamsetji nusserwanji tata – sir dorab tata – nowroji saklatwala – jrd tata – ratan tata – cyrus pallonji mistry – ratan tata – natarajan chandrasekaran –  subsidiariesedit main article list of entities associated with tata group bombay house the head office of tata group tata bus tata nano packages of tata tea himalayan–tata mineral water tata bus in sri lanka thai assembled tata xenon pickup truck this section lists the tata companies and details their business chemicals advinus therapeutics brunner mond general chemical industrial products magadi soda company rallis india tata chemicals tata pigments limited consumer products casa décor eight oclock coffee fastrack youth fashion brand himalayan mineral water brand ishakti infiniti retail cromā landmark bookstores tanishq tata ceramics tata cliq tata coffee tata global beverages the worlds second largest manufacturer of packaged tea and tea products tata industries tata international ltd tata refractories tata salt tata sky tata starbucks a  joint venture company owned by starbucks corporation and tata global beverages ta